## 5. Platform Invariants

These are permanent and cannot be violated even if a feature appears to work.

If any invariant is broken, the review must fail.

### 5.1 Identity Invariants
- Sovereign.os is always the parent platform
- Defrag, Covenant, and Alignment are always spaces, not standalone systems

### 5.2 Shared System Invariants
There must remain exactly one:
- auth/session system
- Baseline Design system
- Library system
- billing and entitlement system
- owner/admin model
- invite/permission model

### 5.3 Storage Invariants
- Baseline Design is stored in KV, not D1
- D1 remains the system of record for shared user/application state
- `workspace_source` must remain the discriminator for saved items by space

### 5.4 Security Invariants
- raw Baseline Design is never exposed to the client
- system prompts are never exposed
- scoring or weighting logic is never exposed
- auth checks remain on protected routes
- entitlements are never trusted from client state

### 5.5 Runtime Invariants
- the product runs on Cloudflare Workers architecture
- app spaces live under `/apps/*`
- `apps/web/app` remains the only app root

### 5.6 Product Claim Invariants
The product must never present itself as:
- therapy
- diagnosis
- medical advice
- legal advice
- expert certainty
- relationship safety assessment
- predictive truth engine

