## 6. Automatic FAIL Conditions

Return `FAIL` immediately if any of the following are detected.

### 6.1 Platform Structure Failures
- Defrag treated as the full product instead of a space
- Covenant or Alignment implemented as separate standalone products
- a new independent auth, billing, Library, or Baseline Design system is introduced

### 6.2 Security Failures
- raw Baseline Design returned to the client
- system prompts exposed in response or client code
- internal scoring, weighting, or field mapping exposed
- protected route loses auth enforcement
- secret-bearing logic is moved into public client runtime

### 6.3 Billing Failures
- client computes or grants entitlement
- Stripe logic implemented outside server-side API worker flows
- subscription state inferred without verified backend synchronization
- fake paid gating or placeholder monetization logic is shipped as real

### 6.4 Architecture Failures
- second app root introduced
- Cloudflare Pages used as product runtime
- direct `.next/` deployment introduced
- architecture splits into multiple conflicting runtime patterns
- duplicate logic created where shared package or shared worker logic should exist

### 6.5 Naming Failures
- “workbench” appears in user-facing copy
- “workspace” used for product spaces in user-facing copy
- “Design” appears user-facing without “Baseline Design” where that product term is intended
- “DEFRAG” used in normal body copy

### 6.6 AI Behavior Failures
- diagnosis language introduced
- therapy language introduced
- spiritual authority language introduced
- prediction or guarantee claims introduced
- identity/personality labeling introduced

### 6.7 Deployment Failures
- build is broken
- workers deploy path is broken or replaced by prohibited production path
- config drift breaks documented runtime assumptions

