## 10. Build Completion Logic

A change can only pass if it does one of the following:
- advances the repository toward the final platform,
- preserves the final platform while improving quality,
- removes drift,
- resolves known incompletion without violating invariants.

A change must fail if it:
- weakens shared systems,
- introduces shortcuts,
- solves one area by damaging another,
- adds “temporary” logic that conflicts with the finished-state model,
- creates local convenience at the cost of platform coherence.

